\section*{Abstract}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Abstract}

\noindent
The rapid evolution of the Internet of Things (IoT) has enabled the development of intelligent living environments that enhance comfort, automation, and energy efficiency. This project, titled NeoHouse IoT, presents a fully integrated smart home and smart parking system designed to automate essential household functions while ensuring safety and convenience. The proposed system uses an ESP32-based architecture to control lighting, fan operations, RGB ambient lighting, and environmental monitoring. Users can operate the system manually, through a mobile dashboard, enabling seamless hands-free control of home appliances.\\
A notable feature of this project is the music-reactive RGB lighting system, where LED strips dynamically adapt to audio input, creating personalized ambient experiences. The smart parking module uses ultrasonic sensors to detect vehicle presence and display real-time slot availability, improving space management for homes and buildings. Environmental and safety sensors—including temperature, motion, smoke, and gas detectors—provide continuous monitoring and automated alerts, ensuring a secure home environment. All collected data is displayed in real time through a mobile or web interface, offering users complete visibility and control from any location.\\
Overall, NeoHouse IoT demonstrates an effective integration of automation, intelligent sensing, security, and interactive control. The system showcases how IoT can transform traditional environments into responsive, energy-efficient, and user-centric smart spaces.\\


\textbf{Keywords:} \textit{IoT, Smart Home Automation, Smart Parking System, ESP32, RGB Lighting, Environmental Monitoring, Real-Time Monitoring, Automation System}


