\pagenumbering{arabic}

\section{Introduction}
\noindent
The NeoHouse IoT project aims to develop an integrated smart home and smart parking system that automates household appliances and provides real-time monitoring. Using an ESP32 microcontroller, the system controls lights, fans, RGB lighting, and environmental sensors through mobile, dashboard, and voice commands. It also includes music-reactive lighting for interactive ambience and a smart parking module that detects vehicle presence and displays live slot availability. Additionally, safety features such as motion, gas, smoke, and temperature monitoring help ensure a secure home environment. NeoHouse IoT demonstrates how affordable IoT technology can transform traditional homes into intelligent living spaces.
In recent years, rapid urbanization and the increasing adoption of digital technologies have created a strong demand for intelligent and efficient living environments. Modern households require systems that not only automate routine tasks but also enhance safety, optimize energy usage, and improve overall quality of life. Traditional home systems operate in isolation and lack real-time monitoring, data-driven decision-making, and centralized control, leading to inconvenience and inefficient resource utilization.

The NeoHouse IoT project addresses these challenges by integrating smart home automation, smart parking management, and energy consumption prediction into a single unified platform. By combining IoT sensors, cloud connectivity, and machine learning techniques, the system enables users to monitor and control home appliances, track parking availability, and analyze energy usage patterns in real time. The use of ESP32 as the core controller ensures cost-effectiveness while maintaining reliability and scalability.

Furthermore, the inclusion of predictive analytics allows the system to move beyond basic automation towards intelligent decision support. Energy consumption prediction helps users understand usage trends and encourages energy-efficient behavior, while smart parking prediction reduces congestion and improves space management. Overall, NeoHouse IoT represents a practical and future-ready solution that demonstrates how emerging technologies can be applied to build smarter, safer, and more sustainable living environments.



% ---------------- PROBLEM STATEMENT ----------------
\newpage
\subsection{Problem Statement}
\noindent
Traditional homes and parking systems lack intelligent automation, real-time monitoring, and unified control, resulting in inconvenience, energy wastage, safety risks, and inefficient parking management. Hence, a low-cost, integrated IoT-based solution is required to address these challenges.

\begin{itemize}
\item No centralized system to remotely control home appliances such as lights, fans, and RGB lighting.
\item Limited real-time monitoring of environmental and security parameters like temperature, gas leakage, smoke, and motion.
\item Poor integration of voice-controlled features, reducing accessibility for elderly and differently-abled users.
\item Absence of real-time parking slot detection, leading to congestion and user frustration.

\end{itemize}

% ---------------- OBJECTIVES ----------------
\newpage
\subsection{Project Objectives}
\noindent
The main objective of this project is to design and develop a low-cost, integrated IoT-based smart home and smart parking system that provides centralized control, real-time monitoring, enhanced safety, and improved user convenience.
\begin{itemize}
\item To develop a centralized platform for remote control of home appliances such as lights, fans, and RGB lighting.
\item To implement real-time monitoring of environmental and security parameters including temperature,  smoke, and motion.
\item To design a real-time parking slot detection and monitoring system to reduce congestion.
\item To predict energy consumption and check parking slot availability.
\end{itemize}

% ---------------- SIGNIFICANCE ----------------
\newpage
\section{Significance of the Study}
\noindent
The NeoHouse IoT system holds significant value in advancing modern home automation by integrating convenience, safety, and energy efficiency into a unified platform. This study contributes to the growing need for smart living solutions by demonstrating how IoT technologies can simplify daily household tasks through intelligent control of appliances, real-time monitoring, and automation. The project benefits homeowners by reducing energy wastage through automated control of lights, fans, and sensors, helping to create a more sustainable living environment.\\
Additionally, the integration of smart parking provides practical advantages in residential areas, ensuring efficient space utilization and reducing user frustration associated with searching for available parking slots. Enhanced safety features such as motion detection, gas leak alerts, and environmental monitoring offer users improved protection and peace of mind.\\
From an educational perspective, this study showcases the practical application of IoT, sensor systems, and automation, serving as a valuable reference for students, researchers, and developers interested in building comprehensive smart home solutions. It highlights how affordable technologies like ESP32 and sensors can be combined to create powerful, real-world systems.


% ---------------- SCOPE & LIMITATIONS ----------------
\newpage
\section{Scope and Limitations}

\subsection{Scope}
\begin{itemize}
\item The system enables remote and real-time control of home appliances such as lights, fans, and RGB lighting using an ESP32 microcontroller.
\item Provides multi-mode control options including mobile dashboard, manual switches, automation rules.
\item Implements smart parking functionality using ultrasonic sensors to detect vehicle presence and display available parking slots.
\item Integrates environmental and safety monitoring through gas, smoke, temperature, and motion sensors for alert generation.
\item Includes music-reactive RGB lighting to enhance user experience with dynamic visual effects.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Limitations}
\begin{itemize}
\item The system depends on Wi-Fi connectivity; performance may degrade in areas with poor network stability.
\item Voice control accuracy may vary depending on background noise, microphone quality, and internet speed.
\item IR sensors in the parking module may produce inaccurate readings in extreme weather conditions or at certain angles.
\end{itemize}

% ---------------- Literature Review ----------------
