\newpage
\section{Literature Review}

\subsection{Synergizing Smart Home with Smart Parking using IOT}
A smart house is a home with online gadgets that allow remote monitoring and control of electrical appliances and systems such as lighting and heating \cite{elhajj2019}. Smart home technology, also known as home automation or demotics (from the Latin “Domus” meaning “house”), that allows homeowners to manage smart gadgets safely, comfortably with less use of energy. Specifically, IoT may be regarded as a concept under which a group of goods/objects may be connected using communication without a physical connection to a wired network, Items can be linked to each other to develop a new job business or even prioritize another \cite{chuang2014}. With local population growth and financial growth, the number of vehicles on the road is growing steadily \cite{vaibhav2016}. Smart parking can be thought of as one of the Internet appliances which can help the car owners in parking their vehicles in a systematic manner using their mobile devices \cite{chen2011}. Smart Parking is a parking solution that can include smart built-in parking sensors, cameras, or counters. These devices are usually embedded inside or placed near parking lots to make sure parking is free and not crowded \cite{wang2011}. Parking is the most important problem for a big city.

\subsection{Applying smart parking system with internet of things (IoT) design}
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Smart Parking System (SPS):}

 SPS refers to parking management system that combines cloud computing technology, database, and mobile devices in parking systems. The system created is not just an operational system for managing parking lots, but also storing information and accessing upto-date information on the condition of parking lots. The procurement of an automated parking lot operational system aims to provide fast, safe, monitored and transparent parking services \cite{fairus2011}.

\item \textbf{Internet of Things (IoT):}

The IoT (Internet of Things) is a computational concept that describes every physical objects can be connected to the internet and can identify itself between other devices. As for capabilities such as data sharing, remote control, etc., including objects in the real world. Examples are machineries, sensors, electronics, collections, any equipment, including people that are all connected to local and global networks through embedded sensors and are always active \cite{ardjuna2015}.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{An IoT-Based Smart Home Automation System}
The Internet of Things (IoT) is a system that allows devices to be connected and remotely monitored across the Internet. In the last years, the IoT concept has had a strong evolution, being currently used in various domains such as smart homes, telemedicine, industrial environments, etc. \cite{elhajj2019}. Wireless sensor network technologies integrated into the IoT enable a global interconnection of smart devices with advanced functionalities \cite{chuang2014}. A wireless home automation network, composed of sensors and actuators 
that share resources and are interconnected to each other, is the key technology to making intelligent homes. A “smart home” is a part of the IoT paradigm and aims to integrate home automation.

