% --------------- Tools and Teechnologies Used ----------------
\newpage
\section{Tools and Technologies Used}
\subsection{Hardware}


\begin{enumerate}

\item \textbf{ESP32 Development Board – Main Controller} \\
The ESP32 is the main controller of the system that manages all sensors and devices. It processes data, controls outputs, and connects to Wi-Fi for IoT communication. It acts as the brain of the Neo House Automation system.

\item \textbf{IR Sensor – Parking Slot Detection} \\
The IR (Infrared) sensor is used to detect the presence of a vehicle in the parking slot. It works by emitting infrared light and detecting its reflection from nearby objects. When a vehicle is detected, the system updates the parking status in real time.

\item \textbf{DHT11 / DHT22 Sensor – Temperature \& Humidity} \\
The DHT sensor measures temperature and humidity levels inside the house. This data can be used for monitoring comfort conditions and for energy prediction analysis. It helps maintain a smart and efficient environment.

\item \textbf{RFID Module and RFID Card – Intrusion Detection} \\
The RFID (Radio Frequency Identification) module is used for secure access control. Only authorized RFID cards can unlock the system, preventing unauthorized entry. If an unknown card is detected, the system can trigger an alert for security purposes.

\item \textbf{Relay Module – Control Lights and Fan} \\
The relay module acts as a switch controlled by the ESP32. It allows low-voltage signals to control high-voltage appliances like lights and fans. This enables safe home automation.

\item \textbf{RGB LED– Lighting Modes and Effects} \\
The RGB LED strip provides different lighting colors and effects. It can be controlled through the ESP32 to create different lighting modes. It enhances the smart home experience.

\item \textbf{Servo Motor – Gate Open and Close} \\
The servo motor is used to automate the opening and closing of the gate. It is controlled by the ESP32 and rotates to a precise angle based on system commands. This allows secure and convenient access without manual intervention.

\item \textbf{OLED Display – System Display} \\
The OLED display is used to show real-time information about the system, such as parking status, temperature, humidity, and access notifications. It provides a clear visual interface for users to monitor the smart home system.

\item \textbf{Buzzer – Alert Notification} \\
The buzzer is used for audio alerts in case of security breaches, invalid RFID cards, or system notifications. It provides immediate feedback and ensures users are aware of important events in the system.
\item \textbf{Power Adapter (5V) – System Power Supply} \\
The 5V power adapter supplies the required electrical power to the system. It ensures stable and continuous operation of all components. Proper power supply is essential for reliable performance.

\item \textbf{Jumper Wires \& Breadboard – Circuit Connections} \\
Jumper wires and a breadboard are used to connect components without soldering. They help in building and testing the circuit easily. This makes prototyping and modifications simple and convenient.

\end{enumerate}

\newpage
\subsection{Software}

\begin{enumerate}

\item \textbf{Arduino IDE / PlatformIO – Programming the ESP32} \\
Arduino IDE and PlatformIO are development environments used to program the ESP32 microcontroller. They allow writing, compiling, and uploading code to the board. These platforms support multiple libraries and make hardware interaction easier for IoT projects. PlatformIO also provides advanced features like debugging and integration with multiple IDEs.

\item \textbf{Blynk - Communication between App and IoT System}\\
Blynk is used as the communication platform between the ESP32 and the mobile application in this project. It provides a cloud-based infrastructure that enables real-time data transmission, device control, and monitoring through a user-friendly mobile interface. Blynk simplifies IoT development by handling server connectivity, authentication, and secure communication. This ensures efficient and reliable interaction between the smart home system and the user.

\item \textbf{Node.js and MongoDB} \\
Node.js is a server-side JavaScript runtime used to build backend services for the IoT system. MongoDB is a NoSQL database used to store system data, such as sensor readings and user activity. Together, they enable data processing, storage, and retrieval for monitoring and analysis.

\item \textbf{Mobile App (Flutter) – User Interface for Control and Monitoring} \\
Flutter is a cross-platform framework used to develop the mobile app for the smart home system. It provides an interactive interface for controlling devices, checking parking status, and monitoring energy usage. Users can receive real-time updates and alerts from the IoT system.

\item \textbf{Firebase – Data Storage, Alerts, User Authentication} \\
Firebase is a cloud platform used for storing IoT data, sending push notifications, and managing user authentication. It ensures secure and reliable storage of sensor readings and system events. Firebase also enables real-time alerts and smooth communication between the app and ESP32.\\

\item \textbf{PlantUML / Draw.io – Creating UML Diagrams} \\
PlantUML and Draw.io are tools used to create UML diagrams, flowcharts, and system architecture diagrams. They help in visualizing the project design and workflow clearly. Using these tools improves documentation and makes it easier to explain system components and interactions.

\item \textbf{Jupyter Notebook and Python – Model Training and Coding} \\
Jupyter Notebook and Python are used in this project for developing, training, and testing machine learning models efficiently. Python provides powerful libraries such as NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn, and TensorFlow for data preprocessing, model building, and performance evaluation. Jupyter Notebook offers an interactive environment that allows step-by-step code execution, real-time visualization of results, and simplified debugging during experimentation. This combination makes the model development process more flexible, organized, and easier to analyze.

\item \textbf{LaTeX – Documentation} \\
LaTeX is used for preparing professional project documentation and reports. It provides precise control over formatting, equations, tables, and figures. Using LaTeX ensures a clean and well-structured final report.

\end{enumerate}


% ---------------- Proposed Performance Analysis Methodology ---------------
\newpage
\section{Proposed Performance Analysis Methodology}
\subsection{Performance Analysis Methodology}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Response Time Testing:} Measure how quickly devices (lights, fan, RGB, parking status) respond to app.

    \item \textbf{Sensor Accuracy Check:} Compare temperature, gas, motion, and ultrasonic readings with reference values to verify accuracy.

    \item \textbf{Parking Detection Reliability:} Test ultrasonic sensor performance by recording correct FREE/OCCUPIED detections under different conditions.

    \item \textbf{System Stability:} Observe continuous ESP32 operation to ensure no crashes, disconnects, or delays.

    \item \textbf{Mobile App Performance:} Evaluate update speed, dashboard responsiveness, and notification delivery.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Validation Scheme}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Functional Testing:} Verify each feature (light control, fan control, RGB modes, parking updates, alerts) against system requirements.

    \item \textbf{Real Environment Testing:} Deploy system in actual home/parking conditions to validate accuracy and responsiveness.

    \item \textbf{Stress Testing:} Run the system for long durations and multiple rapid commands to ensure reliability.

    \item \textbf{Data Log Validation:} Analyze recorded sensor readings and event logs to confirm correct operation.
\end{itemize}



